description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/app_interface/hal_bridge.c:118-134

The switch statement mapping app fix states to HAL fix states is missing LICHEN_APP_LOCATION_FIX_STALE:

  static enum lichen_hal_location_fix_state
  hal_location_fix_state_from_app(enum lichen_app_location_fix_state fix_state)
  {
      switch (fix_state) {
      case LICHEN_APP_LOCATION_FIX_NO_FIX:
          return LICHEN_HAL_LOCATION_FIX_NO_FIX;
      case LICHEN_APP_LOCATION_FIX_2D:
          return LICHEN_HAL_LOCATION_FIX_2D;
      case LICHEN_APP_LOCATION_FIX_3D:
          return LICHEN_HAL_LOCATION_FIX_3D;
      case LICHEN_APP_LOCATION_FIX_ERROR:
          return LICHEN_HAL_LOCATION_FIX_ERROR;
      case LICHEN_APP_LOCATION_FIX_NONE:
      default:
          return LICHEN_HAL_LOCATION_FIX_NONE;
      }
  }

LICHEN_APP_LOCATION_FIX_STALE falls through to default, mapping to NONE.

While valid_app_location_fix_state() (line 136-142) and submit_to_hal_as() (lines 319-323) reject STALE before calling this function, the missing case is a maintainability hazard:
- If validation logic changes, STALE would silently map to NONE
- Compiler -Wswitch warnings are suppressed by the default case
- Code intent is unclear (is STALE meant to be NONE or is it an oversight?)

Fix: Add explicit case for STALE that either returns a HAL equivalent or triggers an assertion.
